<div xmlns:java="http://xml.apache.org/xslt/java" id="centre_col"><!-- begin original content --><h1>ESSUM33500 - Shares to which
schemes can apply: Who must be pre-empted</h1>
<br>
<p>The employee pre-emption provisions imposed by the Articles must
apply to:</p>
<br>
<ul>
<li class="filledcircle">all employees and directors, even if they
are not or cannot be participants in the scheme (paragraph
21(2)(a))</li>
<li class="filledcircle">all cessations by employees and directors
(paragraph 21(2)(a))</li>
<li class="filledcircle">all shares of the class of shares to be
used as scheme shares held by ceasing employees and directors,
regardless of the circumstances in which the employee or director
originally acquired the shares (paragraph 21(2)(a))</li>
<li class="filledcircle">all persons who acquire shares after an
employee or director has ceased "in pursuance of rights or
interests obtained by such directors or employees" (paragraph
21(2)(b)).</li>
</ul>
<p>Paragraph 19(2) does not permit the pre-emption (compelling
shareholders to sell) of persons to whom employees or directors may

have transferred their shares before they ceased (see 

<a href="ESSUM33530.htm">ESSUM33530</a>).

<br>
<br> The most common examples of employee pre-emption provisions

in Articles which fail to meet the requirements of paragraph 21(2)

are:</p>
<br>
<ul>
<li class="filledcircle">The exclusion of named directors from the

employee pre-emption provisions. All directors and employees must

be included.</li>
<li class="filledcircle">The exclusion of cessations for specified

reasons (e.g. on retirement). The provisions must apply on all

cessations.</li>
<li class="filledcircle">Pre-emption being permitted to apply only

to part of a holding. All shares of the scheme class held by

ceasing employees and directors must be required to be disposed

of.</li>
<li class="filledcircle">An &ldquo;all or nothing&rdquo; Article

which provides that if all of a ceasing employee&rsquo;s shares are

not sold, the remainder do not have to be offered for sale (see 

<a href="ESSUM33600.htm">ESSUM33600</a>)</li>
<li class="filledcircle">Employee pre-emption to apply at the

directors&rsquo; discretion. The provisions must apply on all

cessations of all employees and directors, and to all of their

shares of the scheme class.</li>
<li class="filledcircle">Employee pre-emption to apply to shares

previously transferred to relatives or family trusts. Only where

the transferor retains the beneficial ownership of the shares can

employee pre-emption apply to the shares transferred (see 

<a href="ESSUM33530.htm">ESSUM33530</a>).</li>
</ul>
